    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s] </strong>and chop roughly</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Separate your <strong>coriander leaves</strong> from their stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>curry powder</strong> and the <strong>coriander stalks</strong> (reserve the leaves for garnish!) to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth or very finely chopped \u2013 this is your <strong>Sri Lankan-style curry paste</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick, with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>Sri Lankan-style curry paste</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!), then dissolve in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>and your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 8-12 min or until a thick sauce remains</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>diced pollock </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, top the curry with the<strong> diced pollock</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the curry is cooking, chop the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong> roughly</p><p>Stir the <strong>cooked pollock </strong>through the curry and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> aromatic Sri Lankan-style pollock curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-sri-lankan-style-pollock-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>aromatic Sri Lankan-style pollock curry</strong> over the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Top the rice with your<strong> crispy onions </strong>and garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
